<h2>Changes made between OpenBSD 2.2 and OpenBSD 2.3</h2>
d458 1
a458 1
<br><small>$OpenBSD: plus23.html,v 1.4 1999/07/06 21:53:07 deraadt Exp $</small>
@


1.4
log
@its vs it's; hal@@sdsi.com
@
text
@d126 1
a126 1
<li>Merge Kirk McKusick's <a href="faq/faq4.html#4.9">soft update</a> code. This code is still experimental and under a non-commercial license.  It will be included in the next release as an optional compile flag; we cannot ship it enabled by default.
d459 1
a459 1
<br><small>$OpenBSD: plus23.html,v 1.3 1999/06/17 18:46:32 ericj Exp $</small>
@


1.3
log
@get rid of outdated softupdate page, reference the faq page. Valid info from softupdate.html was merged into the faq page
@
text
@d101 1
a101 1
<li>Fix rmd160(3) (and also the IPSEC algorithm) to properly handle data beyond it's block boundary.
d211 1
a211 1
<li>Place separate so_ruid and so_euid fields in struct socket, so that in_pcb.c can still do it's job, but also so that identd(8) can be fast and return the proper uid. 
d373 1
a373 1
<li><font color=#e00000><strong>make readlink(1) terminate it's buffer correctly. <a href=errata22.html#all>This affects CDROM builds so a patch is available for 2.2</a></strong></font>.
d459 1
a459 1
<br><small>$OpenBSD: plus23.html,v 1.2 1999/05/14 03:00:26 aaron Exp $</small>
@


1.2
log
@seperate -> separate
@
text
